      <p>This roundup is based on researched comparisons rather than direct bench measurements. We prioritize consistency signals that matter in daily use: does the adjustment system repeat reliably, does the burr set produce manageable fines, and how much effort is required for a normal 18g dose? Those practical factors usually matter more than marketing claims about burr shape or coatings.</p>
      <p>When two grinders are close in cup quality, we break ties on friction: how fast you can switch brew methods, how messy the workflow gets, and how likely a beginner can get repeatable results in the first week.</p>
